'''URoRRuR'R'R''' was a skilled [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raider]] hunter who once attacked [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] as the latter was trying to find [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] in the [[Jundland Wastes/Legends|Jundland Wastes]].

==Biography==
A Tusken leader, URoRRuR'R'R was very adept at marksmanship and hunting, and also excellent in hand-to-hand combat with the traditional [[Gaderffii/Legends|gaderffii]]. Unlike most Tuskens, he was not intimidated by machines and had no fear of approaching them. He acquired his hunting rifle, an important status symbol in Tusken culture, by scavenging it from the wreckage of a downed starship near Anchorhead. His group raided [[Moisture farm/Legends|moisture farms]] for water and parts and roamed the Jundland Wastes, preying on unsuspecting travelers.

[[File:URoRRuRRRHuntingRifle-ANewHopeLimited.png|thumb|left|150px|URoRRuR'R'R's scavenged hunting rifle]]
After Luke Skywalker had [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] stop his [[Landspeeder/Legends|landspeeder]], and as they searched for the errant [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] R2-D2, URoRRuR'R'R sprung upon Luke with a vicious bellow, knocking the youth unconscious. As URoRRuR'R'R and his followers were beginning to strip Skywalker's vehicle for parts, [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] showed up, expertly mimicking the call of a [[Krayt dragon/Legends|krayt dragon]]. As intended, this unsettled the Tuskens and caused them to flee the scene. However, as Kenobi warned his soon-to-be [[Padawan/Legends|apprentice]] Luke, the Sand People would not remain cowed for very long.<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
URoRRuR'R'R was played by stunt coordinator [[Peter Diamond]], who was the only stunt person on location in Tunisia. As shown in the documentary ''[[Empire of Dreams: The Story of the Star Wars Trilogy]]'', Diamond actually only held aloft his gaffi stick once. Editors [[Paul Hirsch]] and [[Richard Chew]] rewound and repeated this shot several times to make it seem as if he rocked it back and forth in triumph. The famous bellow was then added by [[Ben Burtt]], fashioned from [[Wikipedia:donkey|donkey]] brays.

